Business Brief -- DWG Corp.:
   Firm's Chairman Charged
   With Criminal Contempt
The order, in U.S. District Court in Cleveland, also
charged Mr. Posner with stating falsely under oath that DWG
doesn't pay for his house-cleaning and laundry. The order
requests that the U.S. Attorney for the Northern District of
Ohio prosecute Mr. Posner.
   DWG officials hadn't any immediate comment late yesterday,
and Mr. Posner and his attorney couldn't be reached.
   DWG, a Miami Beach, Fla., holding company, has interests
in liquefied petroleum gas, fast food and soft-drink.